# Belt-and-suspenders against secrets ever entering a Docker build context.
#
# These files are also in .gitignore (so a clean GitHub checkout will never
# contain them), but a developer running `docker compose build` locally could
# still have them lying around in their working tree from an earlier local
# stack spin-up. This .dockerignore guarantees they never make it past the
# build context boundary even in that case.
#
# Rule of thumb: anything that is `.gitignore`d for security reasons belongs
# here too.

# --- Secrets / credentials --------------------------------------------------
**/keystore.p12
**/*.p12
**/*.jks
**/*.pem
**/*.key
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
**/realm-export.json

# --- VCS / build artefacts (size + cache invalidation) ----------------------
.git
.gitattributes
.gitignore
.gitmodules
**/.gradle
**/build
**/out
**/bin
**/target
**/node_modules
**/dist

# --- IDE / editor scratch ---------------------------------------------------
.idea
.vscode
**/*.iml
**/*.iws
**/*.ipr
**/.springBeans
**/.classpath
**/.project
**/.settings
**/.factorypath

# --- Local-only documentation / runbooks ------------------------------------
HELP.md
ToDo.md
.aiignore
.claude

# --- Test / harness leftovers ----------------------------------------------
**/build/reports
**/build/test-results
**/logs
**/*.log
**/*.log.zip
log.txt
